title: Here’s what a 3-year journey to 60 countries looks like (VIDEO)
text:
Here’s what a 3-year journey to 60 countries looks like (VIDEO) Monday August 3, 2015 Print Article 
NEW YORK, Aug 3 — Most of us dream of travelling the world, but how many of us are brave enough to see that dream become a reality. 
After saving money for two and a half years, Walter Chang quit his job in 2011 to act out his very own bucket list. 
From historic sights to amazing landscapes, Chang was able to carry out an adventure that can only be dreamt of, travelling to 60 countries over the span of three years. 
The best part? He has managed to capture the beauty of his trip in this clip for the rest of us to enjoy! 
Many people dream about it, but Walter Chang actually had the guts to quit his job and travel the world over. More Stories for You:
